FT  15 JUN 92 / International Company News: Panini sale at advanced stage
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NEGOTIATIONS have reached an advanced stage for the sale of Panini, the
Italian cartoon stickers company controlled by Maxwell Communication
Corporation, to a consortium of domestic, US and Spanish investors.
No price has been revealed as auditors are still going through Panini's
books. However, Mr Pier Domenico Gallo, an executive of the financial
boutique negotiating the transaction, said a sale could be signed 'within a
month'.
Panini, based in Modena, was bought by MCC for about L200bn between 1988 and
1989. However, the sale price is likely to be considerably lower owing to
the collapse in the company's profitability.
Panini is believed to have lost about L20bn (Dollars 16.7m) in its last
published set of accounts, and has an outstanding debt to MCC of some L40bn.
The consortium, which includes members of Panini's management and
institutional investors, also involves De Agostini, the Italian publishing
and cartographic house.
Although likely to buy only a minority stake, De Agostini may end up as the
biggest single shareholder and take operating control of Panini, according
to Mr Gallo.
