<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUN 92 / International Company News: Euro-equity placing by Sappi is
completed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP GAWITH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG.
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SAPPI, the South African pulp and paper group, has successfully completed
its Dollars 268m Euro-equity placing, the largest such offer by a South
African company since the lifting of sanctions against the country.
The proceeds will be used to finance Sappi's purchase of Hannover Papier,
the leading German manufacturer of coated paper.
However, it is understood that several investors were put off by African
National Congress plans for a mass action campaign, which gave rise to
renewed fears about political instability in the country.
The placing, at market price with no discount involved, was heavily
oversubscribed.
Mr Eugene Van As, executive chairman, said although demand from Europe had
been less than he hoped, he was satisfied with the outcome.
He said Sappi had been forced to cut back severely the allocation to South
African institutions in spite of the fact that Gencor, Sappi's parent
company, had agreed to take up less than 50 per cent of the South African
tranche to ensure a reasonable portion of South African requests for equity
were satisfied.
He would not disclose what portion of shares were placed offshore, but had
earlier expressed the hope that at least half, and possibly more, would go
abroad.
</TEXT>
