executive and a co-founder of the company was replaced, Compaq announced it
would offer products that competed on price rather than features.
Today, Compaq will unveil the ProLinea line of desktop personal computers
aimed at the under Dollars 2,000 (Pounds 1,098) segment of the market, which
represents more than 50 per cent of all desktop personal computers sold in
the US.
US prices start at Dollars 899 for a 386SX model with a 40MB hard drive and
2MB of internal memory, and range up to Dollars 1,899 for a 486DX model with
120MB hard drive and 4MB of internal memory.
The new notebook computers, called the Contura line, come in two models with
US prices ranging from Dollars 1,700 to Dollars 2,500.
