FT  15 JUN 92 / People: DAKS' new style
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DAKS Simpson, which is now owned by the Japanese Sankyo Seiko group, has
appointed a new chief executive to replace the flamboyant pony-tailed Johnny
Mengers who left earlier this year after 40 years with the stylish UK
clothing company.
The new boss is 56-year-old Jeremy Franks, who has been managing director of
the group - which includes manufacturing, licensing, wholesaling and
accessories as well as retailing - since February 1991.
Prior to that he had, since 1984, been running the Simpson Piccadilly store.
Despite speculation, when Mengers went, that there had been friction between
him and the new Japanese shareholders, the company says it has largely been
left to run its own affairs since the acquisition.
But it admits that Sankyo Seiko continues to take a 'close interest' in its
direction.
Kozo Chiba, of Sankyo Seiko, will join the DAKS Simpson board replacing
Yasukazu Saito who retired as a director last month.
