FT  15 JUN 92 / Construction Contracts: Preparing for the Channel Tunnel
link
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London Underground has awarded SIR ROBERT McALPINE &amp; SONS a multi-million
construction contract to extend Waterloo Underground Station in readiness
for the Channel link and to relieve congestion.
The project will provide the interchange between the international terminal
and the underground station and comprises the construction of a 7.5 metres
internal diameter escalator shaft with a bank of three escalators leading
down from the ticket hall to a new lower concourse, the provision of
interchange passageways varying in size from 3.85 to 8.25 metres in diameter
from the lower concourse to the Northern Line platforms, the fitting out of
the new ticket hall and the fitting out of the new London Underground ticket
office within the international terminal area.
Three overbridges will be built over the Northern Line running tunnels. The
shaft and passageways will all be hand mined and lined with cast iron tunnel
segments.
The contract also includes the instrumentation of existing structures and
provision for compensation grouting to counteract any settlement.
