FT  15 JUN 92 / Fierce fighting rage on eastern borders of Nagorno Karabakh
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Fierce fighting raged over the weekend on the eastern borders of Nagorno
Karabakh, the Armenian-dominated enclave within Azerbaijan, as both Azeri
and Karabakh forces attacked and captured villages, mostly outside of
Karabakh's frontiers, writes John Lloyd in Moscow.
It is the first serious fighting since Karabakh and Armenian forces drove a
corridor between the enclave's western borders and Armenia after expelling
Azeri troops from strongholds inside Karabakh.
An Azeri offensive along the eastern Karabakh front on Armenian-held
villages outside the enclave's borders appears to have been a success
initially.  However, a counter-offensive yesterday was said by the Karabakh
self-defence headquarters to have succeeded in recapturing some of the 15
villages claimed to have been taken by the Azeris.
