FT  13 JUN 92 / International Company News: Monsanto warns on second quarter
earnings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ST LOUIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MONSANTO, the US chemicals group, said current results show that
second-quarter earnings may be 20 to 30 per cent below Wall Street analysts'
estimates of Dollars 1.60 to Dollars 1.80 a share, Reuter reports from St.
Louis.
The company said Wall Street had been reducing estimates to that range in
recent weeks.
Monsanto cited costs associated with the launch of its Searle unit's new
anti-infectant drug Maxaquin, inventory reductions for its hypertension drug
Calan and additional costs related to a January plant explosion in Texas.
Mr Nicholas Filippello, chief economist for Monsanto, declined to quantify
the specific financial impact of the three developments.
This year's first-quarter earnings slipped to Dollars 161m or Dollars 1.26 a
share, from Dollars 166m or Dollars 1.31 a year earlier.
