</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JOHANNESBURG's gold index was pushed higher by a rise in the bullion price,
closing up 37 at 1,113. Industrials were depressed again by the threat of
demonstrations next week, losing 20 to 4,591. The overall index was 1 lower
at 3,710.
